Secretary of Transportation Pete Buttigieg, National Economic Council (NEC) Director Brian Deese, and National Climate Advisor Gina McCarthy recently held a virtual meeting with airline leaders to discuss shared priorities. These priorities include supporting the economic recovery, tackling the climate crisis, stopping the spread of COVID-19, and ensuring strong safety protocols.

During the meeting, the administration expressed the urgent need to pass President Biden's American Rescue Plan, which aims to change the course of the pandemic and help airlines and airline workers recover economically. The administration also thanked the industry for their support of this critical legislation.

Additionally, Secretary Buttigieg, NEC Director Deese, and National Climate Advisor McCarthy emphasized President Biden's commitment to modernizing the transportation sector and taking aggressive action to combat climate change. The administration also plans to invest in American manufacturing, strengthen domestic supply chains, and create good-paying, union jobs in the transportation sector.

The airline leaders shared their perspectives, insights, and priorities on the economic recovery during the meeting, and the administration expressed its commitment to building back the economy while addressing the climate crisis. The administration also offered its support to strengthen and advance the airlines' climate goals.